In my opinion LoF has two main appeals: the nostalgic school experience (be it from media from the 90s and into the 00s or personal experience) and the small, abused tomboy female lead. If neither of those are your thing, or you don't like long greentexts, it's natural to not be interested. So nothing wrong with you or the people that like it. Your tastes are different.

HatSSSSS has appeal, I think, because kaktus is good at writing character interactions and because it's a very slow burn with a lot of fluff. That fluff is a selling point to some, and a total turn off and disappointment to anyone that goes into it hoping for a mystery to rapidly unfold. I think the bashing is frustration from anons that got invested before they realized the story moves a lot slower than they prefer.
Throwing my two cents in, kaktus should stick to the path he's chosen and not try to hit the gas hard. He's writing someone else's character. They are the audience he needs to concern himself with.

Both stories are by good writers. Both have anons that meme and shitpost about them. Don't mistake that for anything other than the fanboy-ism that it is. The LoF posters appear to primarily obsess over Sam, a small tomboy, which is no different than crack cocaine to some anons on this website. This isn't to say LoF has never had talk about its plot, but that finished a long time ago and will be less commonly brought up. More interest naturally goes towards characters and memes, especially as art has come in for it in the last six months. Meanwhile, the HatSSSSS posters are invested in something ongoing that receives fairly consistent updates and related art. There is intrigue as to where the story will go and the character of Missy.

tl;dr
We're all autsits on 4chan. Some anons will always relentlessly shill what they like. Give your own tastes more credit and credibility.
